h4. Steps to reproduce

* As a jira administrator on some project, create a new Version called "testVersion";
* In a new tab, add this to a ticket as the fixVersion;
* Back in the jira admin tab, change the name of the Version to "testVersion2" and click update;
* In the ticket tab, reload and notice the fixVersion has changed;
* Open the history on the ticket and notice there was no update corresponding to the change from testVersion -> testVersion2;
* Open the activity on the ticket and click on the link "testVersion", notice that despite the name of this link the "fixVersion" behind it is called "testVersion2";

h4. Expected Results

Open the History/Activity tab and see that the fixVersion field was updated.

h4. Actual Results

Open the History/Activity tab and notice that the field update wasn't shown.

_This is related to all JIRA versions._

